# Slide writing conventions

This rule applies to `slides.md` and any `pages/**/*.md` (Slidev source files).

## Language

- Primary language is **Ukrainian**.
- On the first mention of a key technical term, add the **English term in
  parentheses**: e.g., "обмежений контекст (bounded context)", "інкремент
  (increment)", "специфікація (spec)".
- Keep code snippets and CLI commands in English.

## Slide density

- Aim for **5–7 bullets max** per slide. If a list is longer, either:
  - split into multiple slides, or
  - wrap with `<v-clicks>` to reveal progressively.
- Keep code snippets ≤ 20 lines per slide. Use `{1|2|3}` Slidev line-by-line
  reveal for long code.
- Mark dense slides with `zoom: 0.78` (or 0.86 for medium) in YAML frontmatter.

## Frontmatter discipline

- Every non-trivial slide has its own `---`-delimited YAML frontmatter.
- Keep `background:` and `layout:` in the **same** frontmatter block (a
  separated `layout:` block loses the parent `background`).
- `zoom:` MUST be inside YAML, never in the slide body or after a speaker note.

## Notes & sources

- Put long explanations and citations into HTML comments at the end of the
  slide:

  ```markdown
  <!--
  Speaker note: emphasize that capability slicing is the unit of agentic work.
  Source: https://steipete.me/posts/2025/shipping-at-inference-speed
  -->
  ```

- Do not paste raw long URLs onto the slide body — link with markdown:
  `[programmingmentor](https://www.youtube.com/c/programmingmentorua)`.

## Visuals

- Prefer **Mermaid** diagrams (see `.cursor/skills/visuals-mermaid`) over new
  raster images.
- Reference public assets with leading `/` (e.g. `image: /vyacheslav-koldovskyy.png`
  resolves to `public/vyacheslav-koldovskyy.png`).

## Layouts available in this deck

- `default` — DOU dark background, regular slide.
- `image-left` — `image:` on the left half.
- `image-left-bg-color` — image-left with overridable background color.
- `image` — full-bleed image background.
- `center` — centered content.
- `cover` — Slidev built-in title cover (uses slide-level `background:`).
- `section` — Slidev built-in section divider.
- `end` — Slidev built-in closing slide.

## Verify after editing

After non-trivial edits, run `npm run build` (see
`.cursor/skills/slidev-build-verify`) and fix any errors before declaring
done.
